1) Python program to display all the header tags fromen.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page.

In [86]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
In [2]:
from urllib.request import urlopen
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
html = urlopen('https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Main_Page')
bs = BeautifulSoup(html, "html.parser")
titles = bs.find_all(['h1', 'h2','h3','h4','h5','h6'])
print('List all the header tags :', *titles, sep='\n\n')

2) Python program to display IMDBs Top rated 100 movies data.

In [3]:
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
In [5]:
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import re

# Download IMDB's Top 100 data
url = 'http://www.imdb.com/chart/top'
response = requests.get(url)
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'lxml')

movies = soup.select('td.titleColumn')
links = [a.attrs.get('href') for a in soup.select('td.titleColumn a')]
crew = [a.attrs.get('title') for a in soup.select('td.titleColumn a')]
ratings = [b.attrs.get('data-value') for b in soup.select('td.posterColumn span[name=ir]')]
votes = [b.attrs.get('data-value') for b in soup.select('td.ratingColumn strong')]

imdb = []

# Store each item into dictionary (data), then put those into a list (imdb)
for index in range(0, len(movies)):
    # Seperate movie into: 'place', 'title', 'year'
    movie_string = movies[index].get_text()
    movie = (' '.join(movie_string.split()).replace('.', ''))
    movie_title = movie[len(str(index))+1:-7]
    year = re.search('\((.*?)\)', movie_string).group(1)
    place = movie[:len(str(index))-(len(movie))]
    data = {"movie_title": movie_title,
            "year": year,
            "place": place,
            "star_cast": crew[index],
            "rating": ratings[index],
            "vote": votes[index],
            "link": links[index]}
    imdb.append(data)

for item in imdb:
    print(item['place'], '-', item['movie_title'], '('+item['year']+') -', 'Starring:', item['star_cast'])

  1. Write a python program to scrape cricket rankings.
In [61]:
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
main_page = requests.get("https://www.icc-cricket.com/rankings/mens/team-rankings/odi")
main_page
Out[61]:
<Response [200]>
In [62]:
Soup = BeautifulSoup(main_page.content)

mens_teams = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rankings-table__team")
Teams = []
for i in mens_teams:
    Teams.append(i.text.replace("\n"," "))

mens_matches = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-center-text")
Matches = []
for i in mens_matches:
    Matches.append(i.text)
     
mens_points = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-center-text")
Points = []
for i in mens_points:
    Points.append(i.text)
                 
mens_rating = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-text-right rating")
Rating = []
for i in mens_rating:
    Rating.append(i.text)
    
import pandas as pd
ODI = pd.DataFrame({})
ODI['TEAMS'] = Teams[0:10]
ODI['MATCHES'] = Matches[0:20:2]
ODI['POINTS'] = Points[1:20:2]               
ODI['RATING'] = Rating[0:10]
ODI.index+=1
ODI

In [63]:
Rows = Soup.find_all("td")

rank, teams, matches, points, rating = [],[],[],[],[]

dict_ = {0:rank, 1:teams, 2:matches, 3:points, 4:rating}

for i,j in enumerate(Rows):
    dict_[i%5].append(j.text.replace("\n"," ").strip())
    
dict_1 = {
          'RANK' : rank[:10],
          'TEAMS' : teams[:10],
          'MATCHES' : matches[:10],
          'POINTS' : points[:10],
          'RATING' : rating[:10]
                                     }
import pandas as pd
ODI_1 = pd.DataFrame(dict_1)
ODI_1.index+=1
ODI_1

Soup = BeautifulSoup(batting_page.content)
    
player = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rankings-table__name name")
Player = []
for i in player:
    Player.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

team = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell nationality-logo rankings-table__team")
Team = []
for i in team:
    Team.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

rating = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rating")
Rating = []
for i in rating:
    Rating.append(i.text)
Rating

import pandas as pd
ODI_Batsmen = pd.DataFrame({})
ODI_Batsmen['BATSMEN'] = Player[0:10]
ODI_Batsmen['TEAM'] = Team[0:10]
ODI_Batsmen['RATING'] = Rating[0:10]

Rows = soup_5.find_all("td")

rank, player_name, team, rating, career_best = [],[],[],[],[]

dict_ = {0:rank, 1:player_name, 2:team, 3:rating, 4:career_best}

for i,j in enumerate(Rows):
    dict_[i%5].append(j.text.replace("\n"," ").strip())
    
dict_1 = {
          "RANK" : rank[:10],
          "BATSMEN" : player_name[:10],
          "TEAM" : team[:10],
          "RATING" : rating[:10],
          "CAREER BEST" : career_best[:10]
                                     }    

import pandas as pd
ODI_Batsmen = pd.DataFrame(dict_1)
ODI_Batsmen.index+=1
ODI_Batsmen

Team = []
for i in team:
    Team.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

Rating = []
for i in rating:
    Rating.append(i.text)
Rating

rank, player_name, team, rating, career_best = [],[],[],[],[]

dict_ = {0:rank, 1:player_name, 2:team, 3:rating, 4:career_best}

for i,j in enumerate(Rows):
    dict_[i%5].append(j.text.replace("\n"," ").strip())

          "RANK" : rank[:10],
          "BOWLERS" : player_name[:10],
          "TEAM" : team[:10],
          "RATING" : rating[:10],
          "CAREER BEST" : career_best[:10]

teams = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rankings-table__team")
Teams = []
for i in teams:
    Teams.append(i.text.replace("\n"," "))

matches = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-center-text")
Matches = []
for i in matches:
    Matches.append(i.text)
Matches[0::2]

points = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-center-text")
Points = []
for i in points:
    Points.append(i.text)
Points[1::2]

rating = Soup.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell u-text-right rating")
Rating = []
for i in rating:
    Rating.append(i.text)

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
page_9 = requests.get("https://www.icc-cricket.com/rankings/womens/player-rankings/odi/all-rounder")
page_9

soup_9 = BeautifulSoup(page_9.content)

players = soup_9.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rankings-table__name name")
Players = []
for i in players:
    Players.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

teams = soup_9.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell nationality-logo rankings-table__team")
Teams = []
for i in teams:
    Teams.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

rating = soup_9.find_all("td", class_="table-body__cell rating")
Rating = []
for i in rating:
    Rating.append(i.text)
    
import pandas as pd
ODI_ALL = pd.DataFrame({})
ODI_ALL["WOMEN'S ALL-ROUNDER PLAYER"] = Players[:10]
ODI_ALL['TEAM'] = Teams[:10]
ODI_ALL['RATING'] = Rating[:10]
ODI_ALL.index+=1
ODI_ALL

Rows = soup_9.find_all("td")

rank, player_name, team, rating, career_best = [],[],[],[],[]

dict_ = {0:rank, 1:player_name, 2:team, 3:rating, 4:career_best}

for i,j in enumerate(Rows):
    dict_[i%5].append(j.text.replace("\n"," ").strip())
    
dict_1 = {
          "RANK" : rank[:10],
          "WOMEN'S ALL-ROUNDER PLAYER" : player_name[:10],
          "TEAM" : team[:10],
          "RATING" : rating[:10],
          "CAREER BEST" : career_best[:10]
                                     }    

import pandas as pd

ODI_ALL.index+=1

soup_10 = BeautifulSoup(page_10.content)

product_name = soup_10.find_all("span", class_="a-size-medium a-color-base a-text-normal")
Product_Name = []
for i in product_name:
    Product_Name.append(i.text)

price = soup_10.find_all("span", class_="a-price-whole")
Price = []
for i in price:
    Price.append(i.text)

image_url = soup_10.find_all("img", class_="s-image")
Image_URL = []
for i in image_url:
    Image_URL.append(i.get('src'))

average_rating = soup_10.find_all("span", class_="a-icon-alt")
Average_Rating = []
for i in average_rating:
    Average_Rating.append(i.text)
    
import pandas as pd
Amazon_Mobile = pd.DataFrame({})
Amazon_Mobile['PRODUCT NAME (MOBILE)'] = Product_Name[:22]
Amazon_Mobile['PRICE'] = Price[:22]
Amazon_Mobile['IMAGE URL'] = Image_URL[:22]
Amazon_Mobile['AVERAGE RATING'] = Average_Rating[:22]
Amazon_Mobile.index+=1
Amazon_Mobile

page_11

In [81]:
soup_11 = BeautifulSoup(page_11.content)

period = soup_11.find_all("p", class_="period-name")
Period = []
for i in period:
    Period.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

short = soup_11.find_all("p", class_="short-desc")
Short = []
for i in short:
    Short.append(i.text)

temp = soup_11.find_all("p", class_=["temp temp-high","temp temp-low"])
Temp = []
for i in temp:
    Temp.append(i.text)

desc = soup_11.find_all("div", class_="col-sm-10 forecast-text")
Desc = []
for i in desc:
    Desc.append(i.text)

import pandas as pd
SanFran = pd.DataFrame({})
SanFran['PERIOD'] = Period[:9]
SanFran['SHORT DESCRIPTION'] = Short[:9]
SanFran['TEMPERATURE'] = Temp[:9]
SanFran['FULL DESCRIPTION'] = Desc[:9]
SanFran.index+=1
SanFran

soup_12 = BeautifulSoup(jobs.content)

job_title = soup_12.find_all("div", class_="heading_4_5 profile")
Job_Title = []
for i in job_title:
    Job_Title.append(i.text.replace("\n",""))

company_name = soup_12.find_all("div", class_="heading_6 company_name")
Company_Name = []
for i in company_name:
    Company_Name.append(i.text.replace("\n","").strip())

ctc = soup_12.find_all("div", class_="item_body")
CTC = []
for i in ctc:  
    CTC.append(i.text)

CTC_New = []
for i in CTC:
    if 'LPA' in i:
        CTC_New.append(i.strip())
        
applydate = soup_12.find_all("div", class_="item_body")
ApplyDate=[]
for i in range(2,len(applydate),3):
    x = (str(applydate[i]).split('>'))
    ApplyDate.append(x[1].split('<')[0])

import pandas as pd
Fresher_Job = pd.DataFrame({})
Fresher_Job['JOB TITLE'] = Job_Title
Fresher_Job['COMPANY NAME'] = Company_Name
Fresher_Job['CTC'] = CTC_New
Fresher_Job['APPLY DATE'] = ApplyDate
Fresher_Job.index+=1
Fresher_Job
